2026-01-23.summary:
On January 23, 2026, in Kansas alone, five bills were introduced to the House of Representatives: HB 2538 regarding criminal liability and mental health exceptions; HB 2537 concerning increased penalties for sexual extortion involving minors or dependent adults; HB 2536 mandating training completion by guardians appointed for certain vulnerable adults with cognitive impairments or neurological conditions; HB 2535 providing legal exemptions related to catching feral cats, vaccination, and sterilization. Additionally, a congratulatory bill (HR 6022) was introduced for the Kansas Teacher of the Year team in Congress.

In the U.S. House of Representatives, no new bills were reported on that day, as indicated by empty entries under 'House' and an absence of action from the Senate within both chambers at this time.

Total count overview: Kansas Legislature - 5 introduced; Congress - No activity noted for either chamber.
